1. Community Guidelines
First and foremost, please read the following simple rules, which we refer as "Community Guidelines". See the full doc
here
.
Wakie is a pseudonymous service, where you can use either your real name or any available nickname and avatar picture in accordance with these Terms.
We track the quality of Wakie service. We urge you to:
Be polite to other users. Don't forget that Wakie is a service for kind and friendly people;
Don't be intrusive and don't fool other users;
Don't use Wakie to promote products and services;
Don't post any abusive, illegal, obscene or pornographic material;
Don't post material without permission from its owner;
Don't try to record your conversations.
If you get bullied or just can't stand someone in the community you can block them and you will never see them again. So if you can't build a constructive discussion don't fight back. Just hide everything from that user.
We moderate users carefully. If a user misbehaves and breaks the rules you can report them and moderators will review the case.
By inviting your friends to Wakie you confirm that they consent to receiving an invite.
The wake up call feature disclaimer. We understand that you depend on Wakie to wake you up, and do our best to call you on time. Please note:
Calls will be received with an accuracy of ± 5 minutes;
Even if no users are currently available, our robot will call and wake you up;
We cannot be responsible if the call fails due to technical problems, reception issues, device failure or other issues.
Your mobile phone numbers are securely stored and are not disclosed to other users. We strongly recommend you to not publish your phone number in public sections of the Wakie app. The numbers can be stolen and used for spam. We are not responsible for the publication of telephone numbers by the users and reserve the right to delete these messages.
